</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:1">
<td width="103" rowspan="2" valign="top" style="width:77.4pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Satisfy essential conditions</b></p>
</td>
<td width="228" valign="top" style="width:171.0pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Identify essential conditions</p>
</td>
<td width="259" valign="top" style="width:194.4pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">When all the PARTICIPANTS come together essential CONDITIONS, like what groups should be involved, what are the key customers and what are the key suppliers, can be identified.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:2">
<td width="228" valign="top" style="width:171.0pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Take action to satisfy conditions</p>
</td>
<td width="259" valign="top" style="width:194.4pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">For Technology Roadmapping to succeed CONDITIONS from the PARTICIPANTS must be satisfied.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:3">
<td width="103" valign="top" style="width:77.4pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Provide leadership / sponsorship</b></p>
</td>
<td width="228" valign="top" style="width:171.0pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"></p>
</td>
<td width="259" valign="top" style="width:194.4pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">The part of LEADERSHIP / SPONSORSHIP should be taken by line organization; they must drive the Roadmapping process and use the roadmap to make resource allocation decisions.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:4">
<td width="103" rowspan="4" valign="top" style="width:77.4pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Define the scope and boundaries for the technology roadmap</b></p>
</td>
<td width="228" valign="top" style="width:171.0pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Clearly state vision</p>
</td>
<td width="259" valign="top" style="width:194.4pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">The already existing VISION has to be clear</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:5">
<td width="228" valign="top" style="width:171.0pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Develop vision</p>
</td>
<td width="259" valign="top" style="width:194.4pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">The VISION is developed and stated clearly.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:6">
<td width="228" valign="top" style="width:171.0pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Define scope</p>
</td>
<td width="259" valign="top" style="width:194.4pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">The SCOPE of the project can further define the set of NEEDS, PLANNING HORIZION and level of DETAIL. The scope can be further divided into the TECHNOLOGY SCOPE and the PARTICIPATION SCOPE</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:7;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes">
<td width="228" valign="top" style="width:171.0pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Define boundaries</p>
</td>
<td width="259" valign="top" style="width:194.4pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Also the BOUNDARIES should be included</p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><a name="Phase_2:_Development_phase" id="Phase_2:_Development_phase"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Phase 2: Development phase">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Phase 2: Development phase</span></h2>
<p>The second phase, the development of the technology roadmap phase (see figure 3.), consists of 7 steps: <i>identify the “product” that will be the focus of the roadmap, identify the critical system requirements and their targets, specify the major technology areas, specify the technology drivers and their targets, identify technology alternatives and their timelines, recommend the technology alternatives that should be pursued and create the technology roadmap report</i>. These steps create the actual roadmap.</p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:982px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Phase2.3_Process_Data_Model.jpg" class="image" title="Figure 3. The process-data model of the development phase."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b4/Phase2.3_Process_Data_Model.jpg/980px-Phase2.3_Process_Data_Model.jpg" width="980" height="949" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Phase2.3_Process_Data_Model.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Figure 3. The process-data model of the development phase.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><a name="Identify_the_.E2.80.9Cproduct.E2.80.9D_that_will_be_the_focus_of_the_roadmap" id="Identify_the_.E2.80.9Cproduct.E2.80.9D_that_will_be_the_focus_of_the_roadmap"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Identify the “product” that will be the focus of the roadmap">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Identify the “product” that will be the focus of the roadmap</span></h3>
<p>In this step the common product needs are identified and should be agreed on by all the participants. This is important to get the acceptance of all groups for the process. In case of uncertainty of the product needs <a href="/wiki/Scenario_planning" title="Scenario planning">scenario-based planning</a> can be used to determine the common product needs. In figure 3. can be seen that the participants and the possibly the scenario-based planning provide the common product needs.</p>
<p><a name="Identify_the_critical_system_requirements_and_their_targets" id="Identify_the_critical_system_requirements_and_their_targets"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Identify the critical system requirements and their targets">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Identify the critical system requirements and their targets</span></h3>
<p>Once it is decided what needs to be roadmapped the critical <a href="/wiki/System_requirements" title="System requirements">system requirements</a> can be identified, they provide the overall framework for the technology roadmap. The requirements can have targets (as an attribute in figure 3.) like reliability and costs.</p>
<p><a name="Specify_the_major_technology_areas" id="Specify_the_major_technology_areas"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Specify the major technology areas">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Specify the major technology areas</span></h3>
<p>These are the areas which can help achieve the critical system requirements. For each technology area several <a href="/wiki/Technology" title="Technology">technologies</a> can be found. Example technology areas are: Market assessment, Crosscutting technology, Component development and System development.</p>
<p><a name="Specify_the_technology_drivers_and_their_targets" id="Specify_the_technology_drivers_and_their_targets"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Specify the technology drivers and their targets">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Specify the technology drivers and their targets</span></h3>
<p>In this step the critical system requirements from step <i>Identify the critical system requirements and their targets</i> are transformed into technology drivers (with targets) for the specific technology area. These drivers are the critical variables that will determine which technology alternatives are selected. The drivers depend on the technology areas but they relate to how the technology addresses the critical system requirements.</p>
<p><a name="Identify_Technology_alternatives_and_their_timelines" id="Identify_Technology_alternatives_and_their_timelines"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Identify Technology alternatives and their timelines">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Identify Technology alternatives and their timelines</span></h3>
<p>At this point the technology drivers and their targets are specified and the technology alternatives that can satisfy those targets should be specified. For each of the alternatives a timeline should be estimated for how it will mature with respect to the technology driver targets.</p>
<p><a name="Time" id="Time"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Time">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Time</span></h4>
<p>This factor can be adapted suitable for the particular situation. The time horizons for <a href="/wiki/E-commerce" title="E-commerce" class="mw-redirect">E-commerce</a> and <a href="/wiki/Software" title="Software" class="mw-redirect">software</a> related sectors are usually short. Other distinctions can be made on scale and intervals.</p>
<p><a name="Recommend_the_technology_alternatives_that_should_be_pursued" id="Recommend_the_technology_alternatives_that_should_be_pursued"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Recommend the technology alternatives that should be pursued">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Recommend the technology alternatives that should be pursued</span></h3>
<p>Because the alternatives may differ in costs, timeline etc. a selection has to be made of the alternatives. These will be the alternatives to be pursued in figure 3. In this step a lot of trade-off has to be made between different alternatives for different targets, performance over costs and even target over target.</p>
<p><a name="Create_the_technology_roadmap_report" id="Create_the_technology_roadmap_report"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Create the technology roadmap report">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Create the technology roadmap report</span></h3>
<p>At this point the technology roadmap is finished. In figure 3, it can be seen that the technology roadmap report consists of 5 parts: the identification and description of each technology area, critical factors in the roadmap, unaddressed areas, <a href="/wiki/Implementation" title="Implementation">implementation</a> recommendations and technical recommendations. The report can also include additional information. In table 2. all the different sub-activities of the development phase can be seen.</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span class="GramE"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt">Table 2.</span></b></span> <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt"><span class="GramE">Activity table for the Development phase.</span></span></b></p>
<table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-yfti-tbllook:480;mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;mso-border-insideh: .5pt solid windowtext;mso-border-insidev:.5pt solid windowtext">
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes">
<td width="115" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;background:#CCCCCC;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Activity</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;background:#CCCCCC;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Sub-Activity</b></p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;background:#CCCCCC;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Description</b></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:1">
<td width="115" rowspan="3" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Identify the “product” that will be the focus of the roadmap</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Identify needs</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">This critical step is to get the participants to identify and agree on the COMMON PRODUCT NEEDS. This is important to get their buy-in and acceptance.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:2">
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Use Scenario-based planning</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">If there is major uncertainty about the COMMON PRODUCT NEEDS SCENARIO-BASED PLANNING can be used. Each scenario must be reasonable, internally consistent and comparable with the other scenarios.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:3">
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">State needs</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">These are the NEEDS for the product.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:4">
<td width="115" rowspan="2" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Identify the critical system requirements and their targets</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Define critical system requirements</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">The CRITICAL SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS provide the overall framework for the roadmap and are high-level dimensions to which the technologies relate. These include things like reliability and costs.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:5">
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Define targets</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">For each of the system requirements TARGETS have to be defined.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:6">
<td width="115" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Specify the major technology areas</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Transform requirements into technology oriented drivers</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">The major TECHNOLOGY AREAS should be specified to help achieve the CRITICAL SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS for the product. The CRITICAL SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS are then transformed into TECHNOLOGY DRIVERS for the specific TECHNOLOGY AREAS.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:7">
<td width="115" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Specify the technology drivers and their targets</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Select technology alternatives with their targets</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">TECHNOLOGY DRIVERS and their TARGETS are set based on the CRITICAL SYSTEM REQUIREMENT TARGETS. It specifies how viable TECHNOLOGY ALTERNATIVES must be to perform by a certain date. From the available TECHNOLOGY ALTERNATIVES a selection has to be made.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:8">
<td width="115" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Identify technology alternatives and their timelines</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Identify alternatives and their timelines</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">The TECHNOLOGY ALTERNATIVES that can satisfy the TARGETS must be identified. Next to this the TIMELINE from each alternative has to be identified.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:9">
<td width="115" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Recommend the technology alternatives that should be pursued</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Select subset of technology alternatives to be pursued</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Determine which TECHNOLOGY ALTERNATIVE TO PURSUE and when to shift to a different TECHNOLOGY. Consolidate the best information and develop consensus from many experts.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow:10;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes">
<td width="115" valign="top" style="width:86.35pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Create the technology roadmap report</b></p>
</td>
<td width="192" valign="top" style="width:143.9pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Create the report</p>
</td>
<td width="283" valign="top" style="width:212.55pt;border-top:none;border-left: none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt">
<p class="MsoNormal">Here the actual TECHNOLOGY ROADMAP REPORT is created. This report includes: IDENTIFICATION AND DESCRIPTION THE TECHNOLOGY, CRITICAL FACTOR, UNADDRESSED AREA, and IMPLEMENTATION RECOMMENDATION AND TECHNICAL RECOMMENDATION.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><a name="Phase_3:_Follow-up_activity_phase" id="Phase_3:_Follow-up_activity_phase"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Phase 3: Follow-up activity phase">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Phase 3: Follow-up activity phase</span></h2>
<p>This is the moment when the roadmap must be critiqued, validated and hopefully accepted by the group that will be involved in any implementation. For this a plan needs to be developed using the technology roadmap. Next there must be a periodical review and update point, because the needs from the participants and the technologies are evolving.</p>
<p><a name="Planning_and_Business_Development_Context_for_Technology_Roadmapping" id="Planning_and_Business_Development_Context_for_Technology_Roadmapping"></a></p>
<h1><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Planning and Business Development Context for Technology Roadmapping">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Planning and Business Development Context for Technology Roadmapping</span></h1>
<p>The process of technology roadmapping fits into <a href="/wiki/Corporate_strategy" title="Corporate strategy" class="mw-redirect">corporate strategy</a> , corporate <a href="/wiki/Strategic_planning" title="Strategic planning">strategic planning</a> , technology planning and the <a href="/wiki/Business_development" title="Business development">business development</a> context. 3 critical elements should be connected: needs, products and technology.</p>
<p><a name="Knowledge_and_skills_required" id="Knowledge_and_skills_required"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Knowledge and skills required">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Knowledge and skills required</span></h2>
<p><a name="Consultant_with_skills" id="Consultant_with_skills"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Consultant with skills">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Consultant with skills</span></h3>
<p>In order to create a technology roadmap it is required to have a certain set of knowledge and skills. This means that some of the participants must know the process of technology roadmapping. Next to this group-process and interpersonal skills are required since the process includes a lot of discussions and finding out what the common need is. If the amount of participants is really large there might be need for a <a href="/wiki/Consultant" title="Consultant">consultant</a> or facilitator.</p>
<p><a name="The_variety_in_technology_Roadmapping_.28some_examples.29" id="The_variety_in_technology_Roadmapping_.28some_examples.29"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: The variety in technology Roadmapping (some examples)">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">The variety in technology Roadmapping (some examples)</span></h2>
<p><a name="The_purpose_of_technology_Roadmapping" id="The_purpose_of_technology_Roadmapping"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: The purpose of technology Roadmapping">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">The purpose of technology Roadmapping</span></h3>
<p><a name="Product_planning:" id="Product_planning:"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Product planning:">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Product planning:</span></h4>
<p>This is the most common type of a technology roadmap; linking the insertion of technologies into products. This can overlap between generations.</p>
<p><a name="Programme_planning:" id="Programme_planning:"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: Programme planning:">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Programme planning:</span></h3>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:442px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Purpose_programme_planning.jpg" class="image" title="Figure 5. Programme planning example."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/9f/Purpose_programme_planning.jpg" width="440" height="218" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">Figure 5. Programme planning example.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>This type is more directed to the implementation of strategy and related to project planning. Figure 5 shows the relationships between technology development phases, programme phases and milestones.</p>
<p><a name="The_formats_of_technology_Roadmapping" id="The_formats_of_technology_Roadmapping"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: The formats of technology Roadmapping">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">The formats of technology Roadmapping</span></h3>
<p><a name="Bars:" id="Bars:"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section: Bars:">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Bars:</span></h4>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:404px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Format_bars.jpg" class="image" title="Figure 6. Bars example."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d9/Format_bars.jpg" width="402" height="279" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">Figure 6. Bars example.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Almost all the roadmaps are (partly) expressed in bars for each layer. This makes the roadmaps very simple and unified, which makes the communication and integration easier.</p>
<p><a name="Graphs" id="Graphs"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Technology_roadmap&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Graphs">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Graphs</span></h4>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:404px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Format_graphs.jpg" class="image" title="Figure 7. Graphs example."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/1/13/Format_graphs.jpg" width="402" height="279" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">Figure 7. Graphs example.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Also a technology roadmap can be expressed as a graph, usually one for each of the sub layers. (e.g. IMEC uses the second method.</p>
<p><br /></p>
